= Introduction

The Centurion CPU6 is an 8/16-bit microcoded minicomputer processor
produced by Warrex Computer Corporation. Its architecture descends from
the El Dorado Electrodata EE200 and evolved through three documented
generations: CPU4, CPU5, and CPU6. This manual describes the CPU6;
differences in earlier generations are annotated where known (see the
differences appendix).

